  <!-- AI Summary — 30-50 words -->
  <div class="bg-navy/5 border-l-4 border-gold rounded-r-lg p-4 mb-6 not-prose">
    <p class="text-sm text-text-light leading-relaxed italic">The Alfa Laval CHNX 418 B31-G is a nitrogen-purged horizontal decanter centrifuge for flammable and hazardous sludges. ATEX certified, 418 mm bowl at 4,000 RPM, 100 GPM rated capacity, 20 HP drive. Dolphin Centrifuge supplies and services the CHNX 418 from Warren, Michigan.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- Operation -->
  <h2 id="operation">Operation</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-6 items-start mb-6">
    <div class="flex-1">
      <p>
        The Alfa Laval CHNX 418 B31-G is a horizontal de-sludging centrifuge built for the two-phase separation of <a href="/wastewater-centrifuge/">wastewater</a>, <a href="/crude-oil-centrifuge/">crude oil tank bottoms</a>, municipal sludge-thickening, industrial sludge dewatering, paint sludge handling, and similar applications. It is a specialized variant of the <a href="/alfa-laval-nx-418-decanter-centrifuge/">NX 418 decanter centrifuge</a>, engineered for processing sludges containing flammable, explosive, or otherwise hazardous constituents.
      </p>
      <p>
        The defining feature of the CHNX 418 is its inert gas purge system installed for nitrogen purging of the operating space, including the container vessel and inlet feed pipe housing. This maintains a non-ignitable atmosphere within the bowl cavity, mechanical seal areas, and casing throughout operation.
      </p>
      <p>
        With a 20 HP motor, the CHNX 418 decanter has a bowl RPM of 4,000 and can process 100 GPM of water with light sludge. The unit generates 3,150 G-Force and is ATEX certified for use in classified hazardous locations.
      </p>
    </div>
